ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. I do something special around bedtime (Ex., I must fold my blanket over the pillow before I can go to sleep)
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 2. I have something special that must be done when starting my day at school/work. (Ex., in the morning I must first hang up my coat, then get a drink of water, then say good morning to my teacher/friend/coworker)
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 3. I must perform something in a particular order (other than routines for bedtime or starting your day at school/work)
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 4. I require going specific routes to familiar destinations
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 5. I'm a ''good sport''
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 6. I have difficulty with changes in my routine/schedule
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 7. I share my possessions
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 8. I am interested in other people''s interests and hobbies
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 12. I insist on sameness
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: 13. I repeatedly talk about, write, or draw the same subjects (Ex., I talk about cars all the time)
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: What is that subject?(I repeatedly talk about, write, or draw the same subjects)
Notes: [flex_q13] greater than 0

ElementDescription: 14. I often pretend to be the same character (Ex., Batman)
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: Who?(I often pretend to be the same character)
Notes: [flex_q14] greater than 0

ElementDescription: 15. I insist on carrying around something with me.
Notes: 0=No or not true; 1=Somewhat or sometimes true; 2=Very much or often true; 3=Almost always or always true

ElementDescription: What?(I insist on carrying around something with me.)

ElementDescription: Routines and Rituals Subscale
Notes: Sum of Items 1,2,3,4,15

ElementDescription: Transitions/Change Subscale
Special Interests Subscale
Social Flexibility Subscale
Notes: Sum of Items 5(REVERSE),7(REVERSE),8(REVERSE),22,23
